ğŸ§­ Overview
PAM isolates privileged accounts and limits their scope, time of use, and exposure.

ğŸ—ï¸ Implementation Steps
1.	Deploy Microsoft Identity Manager (MIM) with PAM components.
2.	Set up bastion forest with limited trust to the production domain.
3.	Configure shadow principals, time-limited group membership, and access workflows.

ğŸ”’ Key Features
â€¢	Just-In-Time (JIT) access
â€¢	Time-bound group membership
â€¢	Shadow security principals
â€¢	Workflow approvals

ğŸ§  Use New-PAMUser and Add-PAMUserToRole PowerShell cmdlets for automation.
