ğŸ§Š 24ï¸âƒ£ Read-Only Domain Controllers (RODCs)
________________________________________

ğŸ’¡ Use Case
â€¢	Branch offices or locations with low physical security.

ğŸ› ï¸ Deployment Steps
1.	Add a new domain controller using Server Manager or PowerShell.
2.	On the Deployment Configuration, select Read-only domain controller.
3.	Set replication source domain controller.
4.	Configure Password Replication Policy (PRP):
o	Allow: Users/groups that can cache credentials.
o	Deny: High-privilege accounts (Domain Admins).

ğŸ” Security Advantages
â€¢	No write access to AD database.
â€¢	Mitigates risk in untrusted environments.
â€¢	Credential caching is selective and controlled.

ğŸ” Use Get-ADDomainController -Filter * | Where-Object { $_.IsReadOnly } to list RODCs.
