ğŸ§¬ 25ï¸âƒ£ AD Schema Extension & Custom Attributes
________________________________________

ğŸ“¦ Extending the Schema
Use ldifde to import new schema definitions:
ldifde -i -f customattribute.ldf -k -j .
Example LDIF snippet:
dn: CN=Custom-Attribute,CN=Schema,CN=Configuration,DC=vlab,DC=local
changetype: add
adminDisplayName: CustomAttribute
attributeID: 1.2.840.113556.1.8000.999999.1
attributeSyntax: 2.5.5.12
isSingleValued: TRUE
objectClass: attributeSchema

ğŸ”§ Use Cases
â€¢	Add employeeID, officeLocation, or customAccessLevel to user objects.

ğŸ” PowerShell Management
Set-ADUser -Identity john.doe -Add @{extensionAttribute15="Level3"}
Get-ADUser -Filter * -Properties extensionAttribute15

ğŸ§  Always back up AD and test in a lab before applying schema changes.

